Astragalus cicer

   [3500.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3500

   Notes
   KILLING T: Very winter-hardy.
   GROWING PERIOD: Long-lived perennial legume.
   COMMON NAMES: Cicer milkvetch.
   FURTHER INF.: It is adapted to a wide range of soil and climatic
   conditions, from drylands with more than 400 mm rainfall annually to
   irrigated soils. It prefers calcareous soils but grows on moderately
   acid and alkaline soils, although intolerant of very acid soils. It has
   good drought tolerance. It is winter hardy. It is slow to start growth
   in spring at low to moderate temperatures (7-18Â°C). It is a long-day
   species that requires a period of vernalization for maximum flowering.
   It is intolerant of shade.It is suited to infrequent defoliation.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Heath M 1985 pp 147-148 [KTMP, RAIN, TEXT, PH]
   Duke J 1981 pp 22-24 [DRA, LIG, KTMP, TEXT, RAIN]
   Steven R and Staberg P 2005 [SOIL, RAIN, PH, TEMP, LIG]

